By PRISCILLA OSAJE ABUJA- Veteran Nigerian actor Kenneth Okonkwo, has resigned his membership of the All Progressive Congress (APC) over its Muslim-Muslim presidential ticket for 2023.The actor made this known on his official Instagram page.He stated that APC’s Muslim-Muslim ticket would permanently destroy the political viability of Christians in the north of Nigeria if allowed to stand.He added that he resigned his membership also in the interest of equity, justice, fairness and peaceful co-existence among Nigerians. (NAN) ABUJA - The decision of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, presidential candidate of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in the 2023 election to run a Muslim-Muslim ticket appears to be causing ripples in the party as Daniel H. Bwala, the party’s national legal adviser, has resigned from APC in protest.… In "Top Stories" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Senator representing Adamawa North, Ishaku Abbo has blasted the blasted All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential candidate Bola Ahmed Tinubu for picking a Muslim as his running mate, describing action as very irresponsible. Mr Abbo has since resigned his membership of a His support group over the… In "News" By EMMANUEL MOGBEDE ABUJA- The Nigeria Democracy Defence Watch has appealed to the All Progressives Congress (APC) and Sen. Bola Tinubu, its presidential candidate against presenting a Muslim/Muslim ticket in the 2023 presidential election.The group made the appeal in a letter to President Muhammadu Buhari titled: “APC’s Muslim/Muslim Ticket in Nigeria’s 2023 Elections:… In "Politics"